
__Those Who Make Memories__ is a book published by the Davis Enterprise on the occasion of their 100th anniversary in 1997.  It is a collection of short biographies of notable Davis citizens who contributed in some way to the life of the city from the earliest days to just before publication.  There is a more extended article on Davis history by Davis native, Mary Ellen Dolcini.  Writers are mostly staff members of the newspaper.  Printing is paperback on newsprint paper.  The book is a helpful guide for learning about city history, understanding the lives and personalities behind names on plaques and buildings, and discovering the character of the city.

Citation:

Davis Enterprise, 1997, __Those Who Make Memories__, The Davis Enterprise, Davis, CA, pp. 168.
